# LogWeave reverse proxy — terminates TLS and forwards to the API.
#
# Set LOGWEAVE_DOMAIN to your public hostname (e.g. logs.example.com) and Caddy
# automatically provisions and renews a Let's Encrypt certificate, redirecting
# http→https. Left unset it defaults to `localhost`, for which Caddy issues a
# local self-signed cert — fine for a quick prod-mode run on your machine
# (browsers will warn), but set a real domain for any deployment reachable by
# others.
#
# The API is reached over the internal compose network (api:3000) and is not
# published to the host, so a plain-HTTP login — which silently loops under
# NODE_ENV=production because the session cookie is Secure — can't happen here.
{$LOGWEAVE_DOMAIN:localhost} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy api:3000
}
